# OpenShift AI Installation Toolkit

This repository is a comprehensive toolkit for installing and configuring **OpenShift** with **Red Hat OpenShift AI (RHOAI)** on AWS, including GPU support, Model as a Service (MaaS), and GenAI capabilities.

## Repository Purpose

End-to-end automation for:
- OpenShift 4.19+ cluster installation on AWS
- RHOAI 3.x (and 2.x for workshops) deployment
- GPU worker nodes (g6e, p5 instances)
- Model serving with vLLM and llm-d runtimes
- MaaS API with Kuadrant/Authorino authentication
- GenAI Playground and LlamaStack demos

## Key Entry Points

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `rhoai-toolkit.sh` | Main interactive menu - start here |
| `integrated-workflow-v2.sh` | Alternative modular workflow |
| `Makefile` | CLI automation targets |

