## RHOAI Versions Supported

| Version | Channel Options | Use Case |
|---------|-----------------|----------|
| RHOAI 3.3 | `fast-3.x`, `stable-3.3` (check cluster) | Latest - MaaS, llm-d, Llama Stack 0.4.2 |
| RHOAI 3.2 | `fast-3.x`, `stable-3.2` | Production with GenAI, MaaS |
| RHOAI 2.25 | `stable` | Workshops, demos |
| RHOAI 2.22, 2.19 | `stable-X.Y` | Legacy support |

**Note**: Available channels vary by cluster. Use `oc get packagemanifest rhods-operator -n openshift-marketplace -o jsonpath='{.status.channels[*].name}'` to see available channels on your cluster.

### RHOAI 3.3 Key Changes (vs 3.2)
- **Kubeflow Trainer v2** - GA (replaces Training Operator v1, use `trainer` not `trainingoperator`)
  - **IMPORTANT**: Requires JobSet operator to be installed first!
- **MLServer ServingRuntime** - Tech Preview for scikit-learn, XGBoost
- **Llama Stack 0.4.2** - OpenAI-compatible RAG annotations
- **MaaS Zero-Touch** - Simplified setup via operator (modelsAsService in DSC)
- **NVIDIA NIM support** - `kserve.nim.managementState: Managed`
- **MLflow Operator** - New component for experiment tracking
- **Dashboard URL changed** - `data-science-gateway.apps.<cluster>`
- **CodeFlare removed** - Functionality in KubeRay
- **Resource naming** - Now uses `data-science-` prefix
- **Feature Store visibility** - Stricter requirements for dashboard discovery

